folder_path <- "../../2_Experiments/2_1_Pilot_Experiment/2_1_2_RawData/pilot_expt_v4"

# "pilot_expt_v4_"csv
file_list <- list.files(
  path = folder_path,
  pattern = "*pilot_expt_v4_.*\\.csv$", full.names = TRUE
)

# 
df_list_1 <- list()

# 
for (file in file_list) {
  file_name <- tools::file_path_sans_ext(basename(file))  # 
  df_list_1[[file_name]] <- read.csv(file)  # 
}
#rm(file, file_list, folder_path)

# 
output_path <- "../../2_Experiments/2_1_Pilot_Experiment/2_1_3_CleanData/pilot_expt_v4"
if (!dir.exists(output_path)) {
  dir.create(output_path, recursive = TRUE)
}

# 
for (file_name in names(df_list_1)) {
  data <- df_list_1[[file_name]]

  # 
  participant_info <- data[data$part == "survey", "response"]
  participant_info <- gsub("[{}\"]", "", participant_info) # 
  info_list <- strsplit(participant_info, ",")[[1]]

  # 
  participant_data <- data.frame(
    subj_id = file_name,
    Sex = as.character(NA),
    Age = as.numeric(NA),
    Handedness = as.character(NA),
    Color_blindness = as.character(NA),
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
  
  # 
  split_data <- strsplit(participant_data$subj_id, "_")
  # 
  participant_data$subj_id <- as.numeric(lapply(split_data, function(x) substr(x[[4]], 1, 2)))

  for (info in info_list) {
    key_value <- strsplit(info, ":")[[1]]
    key <- trimws(key_value[1])
    value <- trimws(key_value[2])
    if (key == "sex") participant_data$Sex <- value
    if (key == "age") participant_data$Age <- as.numeric(value)
    if (key == "hands") participant_data$Handedness <- value
    if (key == "color_blindness") participant_data$Color_blindness <- value
  }

  # 
  behavior_data <- data[
    data$part %in% c("motion_test","match_RDK","RDK"),
    c(
      "part", "rt", "response", "correct", "coherent_direction","coherence",
      "isMatch", "association", "difficulty", "dot_color_final","target_color_proportion"
    )
  ]
  
  #  correct 
  behavior_data$correct <- as.logical(behavior_data$correct)
  #  0  1
  behavior_data$correct <- as.integer(behavior_data$correct)
  # 
  behavior_data$difficulty <- as.factor(behavior_data$difficulty)
  
  # 
  official_trials <- do.call(
    rbind,
    lapply(unique(behavior_data$part), function(part) {
      part_data <- behavior_data[behavior_data$part == part, ]
      if (part == "match_RDK") {
        return(tail(part_data, 384)) # 384
      } else if (part == "RDK") {
        return(tail(part_data, 192)) # 192
      } else {
        return(NULL)
      }
    })
  )

  # 
  final_data <- cbind(participant_data, official_trials)
  
  # 
  final_data$subj_id <- as.factor(final_data$subj_id)

  # CSV
  output_file <- file.path(output_path, paste0(file_name, "_Clean.csv"))
  write.csv(final_data, output_file, row.names = FALSE)
}

copmute_acc <- function(data){
  data <- data %>%
  filter(part %in% c("match_RDK","RDK")) %>%
    group_by(subj_id, part, difficulty, association, isMatch) %>%  #
    summarise(
      avg_rt = mean(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      max_rt = max(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      min_rt = min(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      sd_rt = sd(rt, na.rm = TRUE), #trial
      all_count = n(),#trial
      row_count = sum(rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE), #
      correct_count = sum(correct == 1 & rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      acc = correct_count /all_count, #= /
      .groups = "drop")
   
    
    # 
    return(data)
}

matching_task_analysis <- function(data){
  
  # 
  data_name <- deparse(substitute(data))
  # 
  split_result <- strsplit(data_name, "_")[[1]]
  group <- split_result[c(2, 3)]
  group <- paste(group, collapse = "_")
  
  # 1 ()
  # matching_task_data <- data %>% #
    # filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
    # group_by(Participant_ID, isMatch, association) %>%  #

      # sd_rt = sd(rt, na.rm = TRUE), #trial
      # all_count = n(),#trial
      # row_count = sum(rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE), #
      # correct_count = sum(correct == 1 & rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # acc = correct_count /all_count, #= /
      # .groups = "drop")
  
  # 
  # mean_acc_motion <- mean(matching_task_data$acc, na.rm = TRUE)
  # sd_acc_motion <- sd(matching_task_data$acc, na.rm = TRUE)
  # lower_bound_motion <- mean_acc_motion - 3 * sd_acc_motion
  # upper_bound_motion <- mean_acc_motion + 3 * sd_acc_motion
  # [ , ] 
 #  matching_task_data <- matching_task_data[matching_task_data$acc >= lower_bound_motion & matching_task_data$acc <= upper_bound_motion, ]
  
  # 
  matching_task_data <- data %>%
    filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
    mutate(conditions = case_when(
      association == "self" & isMatch == "match" ~ "selfMatch",
      association == "self" & isMatch == "mismatch" ~ "selfNonmatch",
      association == "other" & isMatch == "match" ~ "otherMatch",
      association == "other" & isMatch == "mismatch" ~ "otherNonmatch"))
  
   # 
   matching_task_data$conditions <- factor(matching_task_data$conditions,
                                 levels=c("selfMatch","otherMatch","selfNonmatch","otherNonmatch"))
   
   # print(matching_task_data)

  # ACC plot (match condition)
  acc_plot <- ggplot(
    matching_task_data,
    aes(x = conditions, y = acc, fill = association, colour = association)) +
    geom_flat_violin(
      position = position_nudge(x = .2, y = 0), adjust = 1.2, trim = FALSE, alpha = 0.8) +
    geom_jitter(aes(x = conditions, y = acc, color= association), width = 0.15) +
    # geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = .15), size = .25, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(
      aes(x = conditions, y = acc), outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.7, width = .1, colour = "BLACK") +
    ylab("ACC") + xlab(' ') + coord_flip() +
    theme_cowplot() + guides(fill = "none", colour = "none") +
    scale_colour_manual(values = colors) + #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +  #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_y_continuous(
    breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)) +  # 0.1
    ggtitle(" ") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = -0.4 , vjust = 2 ))

 # RT plot (match condition)
  rt_plot <- ggplot(
    matching_task_data,
    aes(x = conditions, y = avg_rt, fill = association, colour = association)) +
    geom_flat_violin(
      position = position_nudge(x = .2, y = 0), adjust = 1.2, trim = FALSE, alpha = 0.8) +
    geom_jitter(aes(color= association), width = 0.1) +
    # geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = .15), size = .25, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(
      aes(x = conditions, y = avg_rt), outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.7, width = .1, colour = "BLACK") +
    ylab("RT (ms)") + xlab(' ') + coord_flip() +
    theme_cowplot() + #guides(fill = association, colour = association) +
    scale_colour_manual(values = colors) + #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) #palette = "Dark2"
    # ggtitle("Figure b: RT of Matching Task")

  # Combine plots vertically
  # final_plot <- plot_grid(acc_plot, rt_plot, ncol = 1)  # ncol = 1 
  # ggsave(output_file, final_plot, width = 10, height = 15) # 
  #print(final_plot)
  # ggsave("fig2_matching_task.png", final_plot, width = 10, height = 8, dpi = 300)
  
  # 
  #combined_plot <- plot_grid(
    #acc_plot, rt_plot,
    #acc_plot2, rt_plot2,
    #align = "hv", ncol = 2,
    #labels = c("No overlapping", " ", "Overlapping")
    #) 
  plot_title <- paste0(group)
  combined_plot <- acc_plot + rt_plot +
    plot_annotation(title = plot_title,
                    theme = theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 30, hjust = 0.5))) 
  
  print(combined_plot)
  
  #
  output_file_name <- paste0("matching_task_", group, ".png")
  target_folder_path <- "../3_3_pilot_expt_v4/output"
ggsave(file.path(target_folder_path, output_file_name), combined_plot, width = 10, height = 8, dpi = 300)
  
  # 
  # matching_task_data2 <- data %>%
    # filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
    # group_by(subj_id, isMatch, association, difficulty) %>%  # 
    # summarise(
      # avg_rt = mean(rt, na.rm = TRUE), sd_rt=sd(rt, na.rm = TRUE),
      # max_rt = max(rt, na.rm = TRUE), min_rt = min(rt, na.rm = TRUE),
      # all_count=n(), row_count = sum(rt>=200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # correct_count = sum(correct == 1 & rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # acc = correct_count /all_count,
      # .groups = "drop"
      # )
  
  # **/ x /**
  acc_file_name <- paste0("matching_task_ACC_", group, ".doc")
  matching_task_ACC <- data %>%
    filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
    MANOVA(., dv = "acc", subID= "subj_id",
           within = c("isMatch", "association", "difficulty"),
           sph.correction = "GG",
           file = file.path(target_folder_path, acc_file_name)
           ) %>%
    emmeans("isMatch", by = "association")
   
  rt_file_name <- paste0("matching_task_RT_", group, ".doc") 
  matching_task_RT <- data %>%
    filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
    MANOVA(., dv = "avg_rt", subID="subj_id",
           within = c("isMatch", "association","difficulty"),
           sph.correction="GG",
           file = file.path(target_folder_path, rt_file_name)
           ) %>%
    emmeans("isMatch", by = "association")

}

colors <- c("lightblue", "orange", "grey", "green")

rdk_task_analysis <- function(data){
  
  # 
  data_name <- deparse(substitute(data))
  # 
  split_result <- strsplit(data_name, "_")[[1]]
  group <- split_result[c(2, 3)]
  group <- paste(group, collapse = "_")
  
  target_folder_path <- "../3_3_pilot_expt_v4/output"
  
  # 1
  # rdk_task_data <- data %>% #
    # filter(part == "RDK") %>%
    # group_by(Participant_ID, coherence, association, 
             # difficulty) %>%  #
    # summarise(
      # avg_rt = mean(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      # max_rt = max(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      # min_rt = min(rt, na.rm = TRUE),#trial
      # sd_rt = sd(rt, na.rm = TRUE), #trial
      # all_count = n(),#trial
      # row_count = sum(rt>=200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE), #
      # correct_count = sum(correct == 1 & rt>=200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # acc = correct_count /all_count,
      # .groups = "drop") #= /
      
  # 
  # mean_acc_motion <- mean(rdk_task_data$acc, na.rm = TRUE)
  # sd_acc_motion <- sd(rdk_task_data$acc, na.rm = TRUE)
  # lower_bound_motion <- mean_acc_motion - 3 * sd_acc_motion
  # upper_bound_motion <- mean_acc_motion + 3 * sd_acc_motion
  # [ , ] 
  # rdk_task_data <- rdk_task_data[rdk_task_data$acc >= lower_bound_motion & rdk_task_data$acc <= upper_bound_motion, ]
  
  # 
  rdk_task_data <- data %>%
    filter(part == "RDK") %>%
    mutate(conditions = case_when(
      association == "self" & difficulty == 1 ~ "self_1",
      association == "self" & difficulty == 2 ~ "self_2",
      association == "self" & difficulty == 3 ~ "self_3",
      association == "self" & difficulty == 4 ~ "self_4",
      association == "other" & difficulty == 1 ~ "other_1",
      association == "other" & difficulty == 2 ~ "other_2",
      association == "other" & difficulty == 3 ~ "other_3",
      association == "other" & difficulty == 4 ~ "other_4")) 
  
  # 
  # matching_task_data$conditions <- factor(matching_task_data$conditions,
                                 # levels=c("selfEasy","otherEasy","selfHard","otherHard"))

  # 
  rdk_task_data$difficulty <- as.factor(rdk_task_data$difficulty)
  
  # ACC plot (difficulty)
  acc_plot <- ggplot(
    rdk_task_data,
    aes(x = difficulty, y = acc, fill = difficulty , colour = difficulty
        )) +
    geom_flat_violin(
      position = position_nudge(x = .2, y = 0), adjust = 1.2, trim = FALSE, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_jitter(aes(color= difficulty), width = 0.15) +
    # geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = .15), size = .25, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(aes(x = difficulty, y = acc), outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.5, width = .1, colour = "BLACK") +
    ylab('ACC') + xlab(' ') + coord_flip() +
    theme_cowplot() + guides(fill = "none", colour = "none") +
    scale_colour_manual(values = colors) + #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) + #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_y_continuous(
    breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)  # 0.1
  ) +
    ggtitle("RDK Task")

 # RT plot (difficulty)
  rt_plot <- ggplot(
    rdk_task_data,
    aes(x = difficulty, y = avg_rt, fill = difficulty, colour = difficulty)) +
    geom_flat_violin(
      position = position_nudge(x = .2, y = 0), adjust = 1.2, trim = FALSE, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_jitter(aes(color = difficulty), width = 0.15) +
    # geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = .15), size = .25, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(
      aes(
        x = difficulty, y = avg_rt), outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.5, width = .1, colour = "BLACK") +
    ylab("RT (ms)") + xlab(' ') + coord_flip() +
    theme_cowplot() + #guides(fill = "none", colour = "none") +
    scale_colour_manual(values = colors) + #palette = "Dark2"
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) #palette = "Dark2"
    # ggtitle("Figure b: RT of Matching Task")

  # 
  plot_title <- paste0(group)
  combined_plot <- acc_plot + rt_plot +
    plot_annotation(title = plot_title,
                    theme = theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 30, hjust = 0.5))) 
  
  print(combined_plot)
  
  
  #
  output_file_name <- paste0("rdk_task_", group, ".png")
  ggsave(file = file.path(target_folder_path, output_file_name), combined_plot, width = 10, height = 8, dpi = 300)
  
  # 3
  # matching_task_data3 <- data %>%
    # filter(part == "RDK") %>%
    # group_by(Participant_ID, difficulty, association) %>%  # 
    # summarise(
      # avg_rt = mean(rt, na.rm = TRUE), sd_rt=sd(rt, na.rm = TRUE),
      # max_rt = max(rt, na.rm = TRUE), min_rt = min(rt, na.rm = TRUE),
      # all_count=n(), row_count = sum(rt>=200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # correct_count = sum(correct == 1 & rt >= 200 & rt <= 3000, na.rm = TRUE),
      # acc = correct_count /all_count,
      # .groups = "drop"
      # )
  
  # **/ x /**
  acc_file_name <- paste0("rdk_task_ACC_", group, ".doc")
  matching_task_ACC <- data %>% 
    MANOVA(., dv = "acc", subID= "subj_id",
           within = c("difficulty", "association"),
           sph.correction = "GG",
           file = file.path(target_folder_path, acc_file_name)
           ) %>%
    emmeans("difficulty", by = "association")
   
  rt_file_name <- paste0("rdk_task_RT_", group, ".doc") 
  matching_task_RT <- data %>%
    MANOVA(., dv = "avg_rt", subID="subj_id",
           within = c("difficulty", "association"),
           sph.correction="GG",
           file = file.path(target_folder_path, rt_file_name)
           ) %>%
    emmeans("difficulty", by = "association")

}

analysis_dprime_matching <- function(data) {
  
  # 
  data_name <- deparse(substitute(data))
  # 
  split_result <- strsplit(data_name, "_")[[1]]
  group <- split_result[c(2, 3)]
  group <- paste(group, collapse = "_")
  
  # 
  target_folder_path <- "../3_3_pilot_expt_v4/output"
  
  # 
  data$difficulty <- as.factor(data$difficulty)
   
  sdt <- data %>% #
  filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
  group_by(subj_id, association, difficulty) %>%  #
  dplyr::mutate(
    type = dplyr::case_when(
      (response == "f" & isMatch == "match") ~ "hit",
      (response == "j" & isMatch == "mismatch") ~ "cr",
      (response == "j" & isMatch == "match") ~ "miss",
      (response == "f" & isMatch == "mismatch") ~ "fa")) %>%
     summarize(
       hit = sum(type == "hit"),
       miss = sum(type == "miss"),
       fa = sum(type == "fa"),
       cr = sum(type == "cr"),
       .groups = "drop")
  sdt <- sdt %>%
     #replace_na(list(hit = 0, miss = 0, cr = 0, fa = 0)) %>%
     #mutate(zhr = qnorm(hit / (hit+miss)),
            #zfa = qnorm(fa / (fa+cr)),
            #dprime = zhr-zfa,
            #crit = -zfa)
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = hit/(hit + miss),  # hit rate
                  faR  = fa/(fa+cr)) %>%    # fa rate
    replace_na(list(hitR = 0, faR = 0)) %>%
                  # if hit rate is 1, standardize it
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = ifelse(hitR == 1, 1 - 1/(2*(hit + miss)), hitR), 
                  # if FA rate is 0, standardize it
                  faR  = ifelse(faR == 0, 1/(2*(hit + miss)), faR)) %>% 
    dplyr::mutate(dprime = qnorm(hitR) - qnorm(faR),
                  zfa = qnorm(fa / (fa+cr)),
                  crit = -zfa
                  ) %>%
    mutate( dprime = round(dprime, 2),
           crit = round(crit, 2)
           )
         
  

    #  sdt 
    assign("sdt", sdt, envir = .GlobalEnv)
    
    #  sdt 
    #sdt_data1 <- data %>%
      #right_join(sdt, by = "Participant_ID") %>%
      #group_by(Participant_ID, association, dprime) %>%
      #summarize(count = n()) 
    #print(sdt_data1)
    
    d_plot1 <- sdt %>%
    ggplot(., aes(x = difficulty, y = dprime, fill = association, colour = association)) +
    geom_flat_violin(position = position_nudge(x = .2, y = 0), adjust = 2, trim = FALSE, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_jitter(aes(color = association), width = 0.1) +
    #geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = .15), size = .25, alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_boxplot(aes(x = difficulty, y = dprime), outlier.shape = NA, alpha = 0.5, width = .1, colour = "BLACK") +
    ylab('dprime') +  coord_flip() +
    theme_cowplot() + # guides(fill = "none", colour = "none") +
    scale_colour_manual(values = colors) + # palette = "Dark2"
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +# palette = "Dark2"
    ggtitle(group)
    # guides(fill = guide_legend(title = ""), colour = guide_legend(title = ""))
    
    print(d_plot1)
    
    #sdt_data2 <- data %>%
      #filter(part == "match_RDK") %>%
      #right_join(sdt, by = "Participant_ID") %>%
      #group_by(Participant_ID, association, match, dprime) %>%
      #summarize(count = n()) 
    
    #print(sdt_data2)
    
    #** d' **#

    dprime_file_name <- paste0("dprime_", group, ".doc")
    matching_task_dprime <- sdt %>%
       MANOVA(., dv = "dprime", subID="subj_id",
           within = c("difficulty","association"),
           sph.correction="GG",
           file = file.path(target_folder_path, dprime_file_name)
           )  #%>%
      #emmeans("match", by = "association")
}

compute_std_rdk_motion <- function(data) {
  # 
  sdt_rdk_motion_even <- data %>% #
    filter(part == "RDK") %>%
    filter(subj_id %% 2 == 0) %>% # id
    group_by(subj_id, difficulty, association) %>%  #
    dplyr::mutate(
      # 
      type = dplyr::case_when(
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "hit",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "cr",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "miss",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "fa",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "hit",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "cr",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "miss",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "fa")) %>%
    summarize(
      hit = sum(type == "hit"),
      miss = sum(type == "miss"),
      fa = sum(type == "fa"),
      cr = sum(type == "cr"),
      .groups = "drop")
  
  sdt_rdk_motion_even <- sdt_rdk_motion_even %>%
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = hit/(hit + miss),  # hit rate
                  faR  = fa/(fa+cr)) %>%    # fa rate
    replace_na(list(hitR = 0, faR = 0)) %>%
    # if hit rate is 1, standardize it
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = ifelse(hitR == 1, 1 - 1/(2*(hit + miss)), hitR), 
                  # if FA rate is 0, standardize it
                  faR  = ifelse(faR == 0, 1/(2*(hit + miss)), faR)) %>% 
    dplyr::mutate(dprime = qnorm(hitR) - qnorm(faR),
                  zfa = qnorm(fa / (fa+cr)),
                  crit = -zfa
    ) %>%
    mutate( dprime = round(dprime, 2),
            crit = round(crit, 2)
    )
  
  sdt_rdk_motion_odd <- data %>% #
    filter(part == "RDK") %>%
    filter(subj_id %% 2 == 1) %>% # id
    group_by(subj_id, difficulty, association) %>%  #
    dplyr::mutate(
      # 
      type = dplyr::case_when(
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "hit",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "cr",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "miss",
        (association == "self" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "fa",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "hit",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "cr",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowright" & coherent_direction == 180) ~ "miss",
        (association == "other" & response == "arrowleft" & coherent_direction == 0) ~ "fa")) %>%
    summarize(
      hit = sum(type == "hit"),
      miss = sum(type == "miss"),
      fa = sum(type == "fa"),
      cr = sum(type == "cr"),
      .groups = "drop")
  
  sdt_rdk_motion_odd <- sdt_rdk_motion_odd %>%
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = hit/(hit + miss),  # hit rate
                  faR  = fa/(fa+cr)) %>%    # fa rate
    replace_na(list(hitR = 0, faR = 0)) %>%
    # if hit rate is 1, standardize it
    dplyr::mutate(hitR = ifelse(hitR == 1, 1 - 1/(2*(hit + miss)), hitR), 
                  # if FA rate is 0, standardize it
                  faR  = ifelse(faR == 0, 1/(2*(hit + miss)), faR)) %>% 
    dplyr::mutate(dprime = qnorm(hitR) - qnorm(faR),
                  zfa = qnorm(fa / (fa+cr)),
                  crit = -zfa
    ) %>%
    mutate( dprime = round(dprime, 2),
            crit = round(crit, 2)
    )
  
  sdt_rdk_motion <- rbind(sdt_rdk_motion_odd, sdt_rdk_motion_even)
  
  return(sdt_rdk_motion)
}
